post_text: John Knox will be doing a ‚Äúbox dinner‚Äù drive thru this evening! Drive thru pick up will be from 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m. This is open to the entire community and no registration is needed. Residents can pull up their car and will receive one meal per person in the car plus one additional if requested for someone not with them. The meal will be a bbq chicken dinner with either pasta salad or Spanish rice and baked beans as sides.

post_text:
As we near the end of the school year we have begun to focus on next school year and how we can best meet the needs of our students. Our top priority is the health and safety of our school community. We want our students and families to feel confident that they are returning to a safe and healthy environment that is conducive to learning.

As part of the planning process we have put together a Parent Feedback Survey. This survey is designed to get your feedback on the Online/eLearning that took place this year as well as get your thoughts about the 2020-2021 school year.

We encourage all families to complete ONE survey for their family. The deadline to complete the survey will be Friday, June 5, 2020. (Note: An Arabic and Spanish translation of the survey will be posted in the coming days.)

Click here to complete the survey: https://forms.gle/HpgEnCaNvAqfQqxE6

May 1 at 11:19 AM ¬∑

SOUPER SUNDAY üç≤
May 3, 2020
11am - 2pm

We have had so much love and support from the community, customers, friends, and family that we wanted to continue to give back.
Grace Deno, our employee of 18 years whom is also a school teacher informed us she has some students in displaced situations and in need of resources.
This Sunday, May 3, 2020, we will be featuring our SOUPER SUNDAY!
$8 for any of our delicious soups and a roll! All of the proceeds will go to directly to purchasing items for these students.

post_text:
In case you missed the communications that went out yesterday: The district has posted updated information about redistricting for the 20-21 school year. Revised boundary lines for the primary and intermediate schools are now available on our district website for our families to view.

http://www.northolmstedschools.org/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=63AGGUB&dasi=200

The board of education will have a special board meeting tonight April 9th at 7:00 p.m. as well as a regular meeting which will take place after spring break. The Board is expected to vote on the new school boundaries at the regular April board meeting (after spring break). These meetings are being held virtually and the public will be able to view them live on the district Facebook page. The public is also able to submit questions via email to questions@nolmsted.org.

Our teachers have worked diligently to create 20 days/four weeks of learning for our students. As of today, Governor DeWine‚Äôs mandated school closure is through April 3, 2020, with school resuming on April 6th. While this is a three-week period of time, the district has provided learning for four (4) weeks. Click the link to access these resources: http://www.northolmstedschools.org/Onlinee-LearningResources.aspx

If your household does not have a computer or tablet, the district has some Chromebooks available for at-home use during the school closure (one device per family). Please complete the form below to request a Chromebook. Today, Governor Mike DeWine issued an order that all school districts in the State of Ohio are closed for a period of three weeks.

To comply with the order, North Olmsted City Schools will be closed starting tomorrow, March 13, 2020 through Friday, April 3, 2020.

Tomorrow, March 13, 2020 will be a professional development day for staff members. This will provide time for staff members to plan for the three-week period. Additional communications and updates will be sent out to families.

To stay up to date on all information and updates surrounding the coronavirus we encourage families to visit our district website. A specific page has been created on our district website and includes all‚Ä¶

post_text: The health and safety of our students remains a primary concern. As new information becomes available about the coronavirus, we work to update our emergency response plans and increase preventative safety measures. As a proactive step, the district will be closed on March 17, 2020 for all students. This day will be a professional development day and allow district administrators and staff members to plan and prepare distance learning initiatives should the district have to close for a period of time. All after school and evening activities will still take place as scheduled on this day. Read the complete updated message on our district website: http://www.northolmstedschools.org/protected/ArticleView.aspx?iid=63203U0&dasi=200

post_text: Good morning Eagles! We are kicking off Friday with ukulele club at Maple! Every Friday morning close to 60 students arrive to school early to play their ukuleles. The skills students learn on the ukulele can easily be applied to other instruments. Sometimes the students add the electric ukulele, keyboard, guitar, drums and even voice to accompany the ukuleles!

post_text: Kindergarten students at Birch completed a STEM Fairy Tale Challenge. The students measured hair, built a bridge, constructed a chair, designed a stained glass window, designed a tree and put the 100s table back together. At each station they received a letter. At the end of the rotation the students had to unscramble the letters to find out the secret word was!
